      "versionNonce": 723,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": "THE  'EXTENDED'  PART\nf and h are curves (cos, sin, sqrt, atan2).\nF = ∂f/∂x ,  H = ∂h/∂x   — their Jacobians: the tangent's SLOPE\nat the current μ, recomputed each step. A straight-line tangent\nkeeps the bell a bell — the only change from a plain Kalman filter.",
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "ext",
      "originalText": "THE  'EXTENDED'  PART\nf and h are curves (cos, sin, sqrt, atan2).\nF = ∂f/∂x ,  H = ∂h/∂x   — their Jacobians: the tangent's SLOPE\nat the current μ, recomputed each step. A straight-line tangent\nkeeps the bell a bell — the only change from a plain Kalman filter.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
